ğŸ”¹ 1. Basic Linux / Git Bash Commands

(Used in Git Bash terminal)

pwd              # Show current directory
ls               # List files
ls -a            # Show hidden files
cd folder_name   # Go to folder
cd ..            # Go back
clear            # Clear terminal
mkdir folder     # Create folder
touch file.txt   # Create file
rm file.txt      # Delete file
rm -r folder     # Delete folder

ğŸ”¹ 2. Git Configuration (One Time Setup)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"

git config --list   # Check config

ğŸ”¹ 3. Create & Initialize Repository
git init                 # Initialize new repo
git status               # Check status
git clone repo_url       # Clone repository

ğŸ”¹ 4. Staging & Commit Commands
git add file.txt         # Add single file
git add .                # Add all files
git commit -m "message"  # Commit changes


ğŸ“Œ Shortcut:

git commit -am "message"  # add + commit (tracked files only)

ğŸ”¹ 5. Check Changes & History
git diff                # Show unstaged changes
git diff --staged       # Show staged changes

git log                 # Commit history
git log --oneline       # Short history
git show commit_id      # Show commit details

ğŸ”¹ 6. Branch Commands ğŸŒ¿
git branch               # List branches
git branch branch_name   # Create branch
git checkout branch_name # Switch branch

git checkout -b newBranch  # Create + switch


Delete branch:

git branch -d branch_name

ğŸ”¹ 7. Merge & Rebase
git merge branch_name    # Merge branch
git rebase branch_name   # Rebase branch

ğŸ”¹ 8. Remote Repository (GitHub)
git remote -v                 # Check remote
git remote add origin URL     # Add remote
git push origin main          # Push code
git pull origin main          # Pull code
git fetch                     # Fetch updates


Force push (âš ï¸ dangerous):

git push -f origin main

ğŸ”¹ 9. Undo & Fix Mistakes ğŸ˜¬
Undo staging
git reset file.txt

Undo commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

Undo commit (remove changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

Discard local changes
git checkout -- file.txt

ğŸ”¹ 10. Stash Commands ğŸ“¦
git stash           # Save work temporarily
git stash list      # Show stash
git stash apply     # Apply stash
git stash drop      # Delete stash

ğŸ”¹ 11. Tag Commands ğŸ”–
git tag v1.0
git tag
git push origin v1.0

ğŸ”¹ 12. Cherry Pick ğŸ’
git cherry-pick commit_id

ğŸ”¹ 13. .gitignore File

Create .gitignore file:

node_modules/
.env
*.log

ğŸ”¹ 14. Git Workflow (Real Project)
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin URL
git push -u origin main
